ODE XX.

In this little ode Horace declares that he will not in future heark- en to the dictates of a hurtful passion, to which he had been too long a slave. And it must be said, to his credit, that he did actu- ally give up, at the age of forty, when this ode was written, his former habits of sensual indulgence. Though from what he says, we have some reason to believe that resentment had some share in forming the resolution to do so.
